content.detailedDescription: I was sitting inside our home watching television, when my husband called to me from outside, so i hurried to see what he was yelling about.  when he pointed at the sky i looked up in disbelief.  we both did not know what we were looking at, but it was nothing that we had ever seen before.  we could only presume that it was unidentified flying objects.  i even said, "what the hell are we looking at?"  the objects projected a redish-orange beam in a prism-like diamond shape.  the objects were coming from the s.E. and moving in a northern direction.  a few of the objects stopped, slightly before passing over us, as if they spotted us watching them and stopped to watch us.  next, they slowly proceeded to move in a northern pattern, one following the other and then, they shifted more toward the north east and ascended into the cloud coverage.  we were both left speechless as we walked inside.  my husband also, videoed what we observed.  however, when we looked at what he recorded, it does not look like what we saw, but instead, they look like white lights moving across the sky. after we went inside, i was curious to see if there might be more in the sky.  i went back outside by myself, approximately 5 minutes later.  as i looked just slightly over our house, toward the north, there was one ufo that was stationary before slowly moving to the north east and following the others.  i phoned the police department to see if they had received calls about any sightings that evening, but they said that they had not. they were of no assistance, but were willing to give me the phone number of the jacksonville police department.  i declined.
content.summary: My husband called to me when he observed the ufo's outside.  moving in a n.E. direction, a few of them stopped and hovered over us from above.  they continued to move n.E. and ascended into the clouds.  one returned 5 minutes later and then followed.

content.detailedDescription: I was in bed. it was late. two of my cats had decided, very unusually, to sleep tightly on either side of me.It's like they had an intuition that someone might try to take me away. i heard a very soft female voice, kind of metallic-sounding call my name. i said out loud "that sounds like someone said (my name). then from ahead of me in my bedroom, a louder female voice said my name, then asked "are you ready?" i said out loud "it must be the aliens." then i said out loud "no, i'm afraid". (apparently once they contacted me i had been aware on some level that i had met these aliens before, but i always thought it had been a dream, or i had forgotten.) but they came anyway. these women appeared in my bedroom. they wore what looked like white nurse uniforms with old-fashioned white nurse caps on, and they appeared to be dark haired and vaguely asian human looking. i floated above the bed, and one of the nurses lay down between my cats where i was. the cats were apparently still asleep or immobile. the rest of the aliens who made themselves look like nurses, probably to lessen my fear, and i floated right through my bedroom wall. i think i was on a stretcher. i had some lost time, then i found myself walking with them inside a spaceship. i walked in a circle around a room in the ship. there were many aliens there,all appearing mostly human, who were looking at me. we stopped in front of a dark haired mostly human-looking man with long hair in little braids, like i used to wear my hair. he had light green skin and a large forehead but otherwise looked human. suddenly my hair was in braids again and i laughed and said "i've got braids too."i felt friendly toward this alien man.I think they have the ability to take pictures out of your mind and make themselves and yourself appear different. then more time was lost. when i woke, i was on a table with many of the nurses around it on both sides. there was a white balloon between my legs and off that end of the table the balloon was large. it felt like someone was having sex with me. when i saw the balloon i realized this was not a dream and that this must be an abduction experience.I think the male alien was inside the balloon, almost like a whole body condom. afterward, i asked one of the nurses "what just happened?" she said "what did you want to happen?" i said i wanted a baby. she said you'll get your wish. i asked if humans would notice i was pregnant. she said no, except for thursday. she said it's called the great stink and that my house would stink. i felt at ease with these aliens as if they were my friends and i'd known them a long time. i think the man with the braids was who impregnated me, but it was not his true appearance. i went through menopause 4 years ago but am on hormone replacement therapy. i never had a child, but i had a thought come into my head a few days previously that if there was a way to reverse menopause i wouldn't mind having a baby.In what i thought was a dream, once, aliens told me that i was the only human who was able to receive messages they sent telepathically, and that they sent ten to twenty a day, but that i only received a few of them. i think they put that thought into my head, that i wanted a baby.We talked some more then i blacked out, then i felt myself being lowered onto my bed, right between the still-sleeping cats. i rolled over and went to sleep and remembered everything in the morning. one month later, on august 16th, i saw a red laser beam light on the pillow next to mine. i trembled with fear and said no, please go away don't come. but after a few minutes of lost time, two alien women came into my bedroom. they walked through the outside door, just through it. when they showed up i felt no fear and felt they were my friends that i already knew. they said they were here to give me an exam. this time they did not try to hide their appearance. one was a grey alien and one looked almost human but she had larger than normal eyes and a high forehead. they put a rubber tube around my left arm and asked  if i'd been taking vitamins and hadn't taken any "anesthesias" i think they meant drugs. i said yes i'd followed their instructions. i asked the human-looking one if she was 3/4 human and 1/4 alien and she said yes, 3/4 white. i asked if that's what the baby would be and she said yes. i said "i like that look it's very attractive." they were very friendly to me and after a few minutes, they noticed me looking at the grey alien a little bit afraid and suddenly they appeared to be wearing hoodies. i must confess that after the first remembered abduction i had read on the internet that the grey aliens were doing a breeding program and hybrids were supposed to seed the earth soon. i had asked them does this mean they were able to reverse menopause and they didn't answer. there are other details but i'm getting tired of typing and i'm not sure i haven't said too much already. i have had some signs of pregnancy but so far no positive pregnancy test. i want to get an ultrasound but my doctor would think i was crazy if i asked. can mufon help me get an ultrasound? i would be 5-6 weeks pregnant now and according to the internet they come for the fetus after 9 to 11 weeks and implant it in a female hybrid. i want proof that i'm pregnant and they are going to show me the baby after it is born but i want proof that this isn't just me imagining the whole thing. please contact me. i just woke from a nightmare that government agents were coming to talk to me and that they may not like the aliens. i want to stress that i'm always terrified at first of the aliens, but that after they show up i'm at ease and that they've always been very kind to me and friendly. i like them and i think they are benevolent and only want to help mankind and at the same time save their dying race so hybrids are a great solution.Please contact me soon.
content.summary: Abduction. aliens seemed to know me and called me by name. i remembered them from before.

content.detailedDescription:
As i went out for a late night walk, soon after starting (about a block from my house) i noticed a light in the sky. i didn't think much of it, at first. i assumed it was a helicopter, since those are somewhat common in the general area, especially at night.

but, even at first site it seemed odd. but, after a few seconds i looked up again, and didn't see the usual blinking lights. also, the helicopters aren't usually glowing red. so, i slowed down, eventually to a stop to watch. it seemed like it drifted some, not much. i couldn't tell if it was ascending, or moving away from me. 

it's at this time i pulled out my phone, and took the short vidfeo i did. i have attached it. to be honest, it doesn't show much, as the quality of phone videos are quite lacking. but, i did my best.

so, after about 30 seconds i stopped filming (due to low space on my phone.) and slowly started walking again, keeping my eye on the object. as i reached the main street corner, it was gone. i didn't see it go off to anyside, it was as if the lights were shut off.

i continued my walk for another 20 minutes, or so, looking up every chance i got, but i never saw it again. at the time i did view it, there were no clouds, or other objects in the sky. soon after, an airplane did fly in that general direction, from the south eat, towards the west. but, this was maybe a minute, or two after the object disappeared.
content.summary: Red hovering lights in the west

content.detailedDescription: Rear patio of apartment at a birch street manunda cairns queensland,while observing satellites as we often do, my partner and i witnessed what looked like two satellites of a magnitude -4 or brighter travelling along side each-other in a south to north direction at what was a typical satellite altitude. only, these two objects blinked on with intensity that caused us both to let out a gasp, and an expletive, as we watched the object/s get brighter as they moved, and had a connecting tube like structure between them that emanated a milky glow, very dull compared to the brightness of the lights. the object/s travelled side by side as a single unit for up to 20 seconds before blinking out simultaneously, not to be seen again. this observation took place at 18:44 local time gmt +10 and left us both in awe. we watch satellites most evenings, and are familiar with aircraft and other phenomena, but this was a stirring observation that made us search for other possible witnesses on-line, finding none so far.
content.summary: 2 bright lights with connecting dark beam/tube and milky aura on beam from south to north blinked out

content.detailedDescription:
Santa monica mountains near santa monica area on august 26, 2015 at approximately 1055pm local time i saw very colorful blinking lights to the northwest just above the mountain tops.  at first i thought it was a helicopter using a spotlight off in the distance until i looked more closely and saw how amazingly colorful it was and that there was no sound.  i was in a very quiet canyon and i couldn't hear it at all.  it was quite amazing the array of colors that pulsated very quickly and it was oddly bright, and yet slightly fuzzy like a star (but bigger) seen through low atmosphere, though very clear to the naked eye that it was pulsating colors and flashing.  then i noticed it was moving around in zig zags very quickly.
i have personally never seen an object in the sky move like that and at the distance it was, i don't know anything that can move as quickly as it did and so erratically.  i went and got a video camera and videoed the object and you can see it on the footage moving in sharp shapes and pulsating an array of colors.
i was perplexed and rather stunned that i was seeing something i had never seen before.
this took place for about 7 minutes.  after it moved for a bit it then appeared to remain in one spot.  then i knew it was strange but i thought it might be a star pulsating like crazy due to atmosphere?
there was no sound and then after about 3 or 4 minutes a helicopter came by to my north.  that i could hear as a helicopter, the object never made sound.  
i went inside to check online and figured i would come back in 5 minutes and see if it was still there, perhaps proving to myself that it was a pulsating star.  i went back out 5 minutes later and it was gone and there was no star in the sky where it had been.  i wish i would have just kept filming it, but i was quite baffled all around.
i included a very short video though i have about 7 minutes of it on video. i also included a googleearth view and approximation of my location and the objects location.
content.summary: 1055pm santa monica mountains i saw very colorful blinking object moving in zig-zag lines without sound.
